/ITWe rise for /MDAleynu/XX. It is customary to bow at "bend the knee." For an alternative version see
page 126. For additional readings see pages 737-739, 748, 772-774, 776-777, 803-804.
Choose one of the following:/PR
/PR
It is up to us to offer praises to the Source of all,/PR
to declare the greatness of the author of Creation,/PR
who gave to us teachings of truth/PR
and planted eternal life within us./PR
/PR
#/PR
/PR
It is up to us to offer praises to the Source of all,/PR
to declare the greatness of the author of Creation,/PR
who created heavenÚs heights and spread out its expanse,/PR
who laid the earthÚs foundation and brought forth its offspring,/PR
giving life to all its peoples,/PR
the breath of life to all who walk about./PR
/SCC/XXOMMENTARY/XX. This siddur offers several versions of the /ITAleynu/XX. The first,
which appeared in the 1945 Reconstructionist siddur, emphasizes that the
gift of GodÚs Torah or teaching demands our committed response. The
second version, based on Isaiah 42:5 and fit into the /ITAleynu/XX by Rabbi Max
D. Kline, emphasizes that our obligation to God flows from our role as
part of Creation. The traditional /ITAleynu/XX that appears below the line has
troubled Reconstructionist Jews because it implies the inferiority of other
faiths and peoples.    /SC/XXD.A.T./XX/PR
