/PG122/XX/PR
And so, we bend the knee and bow,/PR
acknowledging the sovereign who rules/PR
above all those who rule, the blessed Holy One,/PR
who stretched out the heavens and founded the earth,/PR
whose realm embraces heavenÚs heights,/PR
whose mighty presence stalks celestial ramparts./PR
This is our God; there is none else besides,/PR
as it is written in the Torah:/PR
"You shall know this day, and bring it home/PR
inside your heart, that /SCT/XXHE /XXS/XXUPREME /XXO/XXNE/XX is God/PR
in the heavens above and on the earth below./PR
There is no other God."/PI/PR
/SCD/XXERASH/XX. Every person and people that feel they have something to live
for, and that are bent on living that life in righteousness, are true witnesses
of God.    /SC/XXM.M.K./XX/PR
/PR
/SCK/XXAVANAH/XX. As the hand held before the eye hides the tallest mountain, so
this small earthly life hides from our gaze the vast radiance and secrets of
which the world is full, and if we can take life from before our eyes, as
one takes away oneÚs hand, we will see the great radiance within the
world.    /SC/XXM.B. (ADAPTED)/XX/PR
