/PG124/XX/PR
And so, we put our hope in you,/PR
/SCT/XXHE /XXE/XXMINENCE/XX, our God,/PR
that soon we may behold/PR
the full splendor of your might,/PR
and see idolatry vanish from the earth,/PR
and all material gods be swept away,/PR
and the power of your rule repair the world,/PR
and all creatures of flesh call on your name,/PR
and all the wicked of the earth turn back to you./PR
Let all who dwell upon the globe perceive and know/PR
that to you each knee must bend, each tongue swear oath,/PR
and let them give the glory of your name its precious due./PR
Let all of them take upon themselves your rule./PR
Reign over them, soon and for always./PR
For this is all your realm, throughout all worlds, across all/PR
time--/PR
as it is written in your Torah:/PR
"/SCT/XXHE /XXE/XXTERNAL /XXO/XXNE/XX will reign now and forever."/PR
/PR
And it is written:/PR
"/SCT/XXHE /XXE/XXVERLASTING /XXO/XXNE/XX will reign/PR
as sovereign over all the earth./PR
On that day shall /SCT/XXHE /XXM/XXANY /XXN/XXAMED/XX be one,/PR
GodÚs name be one!"/PR
/SCK/XXAVANAH/XX. A world of God callers is a world of truth and peace, a world
where the lust for power, greed, and envy--the idols of pride--is uprooted
from the individual and group psyche.    /SC/XXS.P.W./XX/PR
