/PGMAÚARIV/XX126/XX/PR
/KAALTERNATIVE VERSION/XX/PR
It is up to us/PR
to hallow Creation,/PR
to respond to Life/PR
with the fullness of our lives./PR
It is up to us/PR
to meet the World,/PR
to embrace the Whole/PR
even as we wrestle/PR
with its parts./PR
It is up to us/PR
to repair the World/PR
and to bind our lives to Truth./PR
/PR
Therefore we bend the knee/PR
and shake off the stiffness that keeps us/PR
from the subtle/PR
graces of Life/PR
and the supple/PR
gestures of Love./PR
With reverence/PR
and thanksgiving/PR
we accept our destiny/PR
and set for ourselves/PR
the task of redemption./PR
Rami M. Shapiro/XX/PR
